description:
Alphrodite is a masterpiece of French 19th century literature. This classical tale of sensuous love was one of the best-selling novels of its time. Published in 1896, Aphrodite made Pierre Louys famous and was by far his greatest success, surpassing that of his other well-know works such as The Songs of Bilitis. Conceived as a novel of the antiquity focusing on women and on light, Aphrodite lends itself naturally to illustration.

Book One, illustrated by Milo Manara - The story takes place in Alexandria in the 1st Century BC where Demetrios, a renowned artist falls in love with a courtesan, Chrysis. She asks him to prove his love to her by committing three crimes and Demetrios agrees. In this volume, Manara lets his imagination run wild as he illustrates a part of this novel.
name: Book One: Artwork by Milo Manara

By Brian Michael Bendis, Sara Pichelli and Stuart Immonen!

Featuring material first printed in Uncanny X-Men #15-16, Guardians of the Galaxy #11 and All-New X-Men #22-23.

Stop Those Heroes

The April Evil Inc comic is a continuation of the exciting "Ul'Thax Proposal" storyline. The heroes are gathered to save the world - or so they think! Will the villains be able to save the world? The Ul'Thax Proposal promises to put Evil Inc in charge of world domination -- if it doesn't destroy it first!

Then... in a huge bonus feature, we re-live Dr. Muskiday falling head-over-flippers in love with a woman who has a dark, horrible secret. Will Dr. Haynus be able to save him (and will he be able to save himself and his puppy/host Scruffy in the process)?

Now in the presence of The Father of Grotesques the Gideon's only hope are the Katrinas speeding to them. Will they be too late?

76 pages of Marvel Universe adventure!

A new Silver Surfer series begins! The Surfer faces the awesome power of the dreaded Never Queen! Cosmic adventure from Dan Slott and Michael Allred!

An 'Original Sin' chapter! As the scale of the conspiracy is revealed, the heroes turn on each other! Dark intrigue from Jason Aaron and Mike Deodato!

Featuring material first printed in Silver Surfer #1-2, Daredevil #2 and Original Sin #4.

LIBERAIDER & THE LION: Tomb Of Lies

For millennia, the energies of the Zodiac have been available to those whose consciousness is open to the reception and manipulation of them.

That access has been achieved one person for each of the houses of the celestial wheel. This is the saga of the New Zodiax! Each of the first four issues will debut a new member of the Zodiax universe. This issue premieres THE LION--the First Stargazer! Is he hero or demon? Also in this issue, the origin of the LIBERAIDER continues!

Created by Joe St.Pierre (Marvel, DC, Image, Valiant, IDW).
name: Liberaider & The Lion: Tomb of Lies

description:
A group of paranormal investigators with their own television show head to a remote island in the Pacific Northwest to film their season finale. Alone and on their own, they encounter something evil that was let loose upon the island, long ago.

This issue - The demon has possessed the island caretaker and history is repeating itself as one by one the investigators fall to another knife wielding maniac. Will anyone survive to tell the tale of what happened on the island?

A shapeshifting immortal awakens from a ten thousand year sleep to find that the world she thought she saved has been infected by evil. Lost in a barbaric era, her own past may be the key to unlocking the future. Sevara rescues an injured slave girl, only to attract the full wrath of the evil King Mitan. To save humanity, Sevara is going to have to rewrite history!

Playwright and photographer Damian Wampler forges an entirely new universe with Indonesian artists Andre Siregar and Anang Setyawan. Spanning centuries, this totally original fantasy world takes action and adventure to a new level.

Chapter 10

Danny and Pat are enlisted to help save capture woman from Danny's werewolf cousin.
name: Chapter 10

In the darkest corner of the cosmos an evil is building momentum, and if left unchallenged it will soon be unleashed upon billions of unsuspecting lives throughout the entire cosmos.

description:

In part 2 of "The Good Child", Yoshiko is forced to move on from the death of her mother to her pending wedding to the man she had been betrothed to since she was ten years old.

The Forky Trail

Strange tales have the town of Boxtop Hill in a panic! Who is singing those sailor songs? Why is all the hog chow missing? Obadiah Dirt and The Stranger hardly say dangity in this corkscrewed Wee Western!
name: The Forky Trail
